docs.abstract: The attorney general, speaking at a religious broadcasters convention, said Christian news organizations were a vital check on a mainstream press that had become too powerful.
docs.snippet: The attorney general, speaking at a religious broadcasters convention, said Christian news organizations were a vital check on a mainstream press that had become too powerful.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — In a wide-ranging speech on the importance of Christianity in public life, Attorney General William P. Barr said on Wednesday that religious news publications and broadcasters were essential checks on a mainstream media that has consolidated far too much power.

headline.main: Barr Criticizes Mainstream Media as ‘Monolithic in Viewpoint’
headline.print_headline: Barr Calls News Media ‘Monolithic In Viewpoint’

docs.abstract: A bookkeeping change at the department will cut thousands of dollars in aid to some of the poorest, most isolated schools in the country.
docs.snippet: A bookkeeping change at the department will cut thousands of dollars in aid to some of the poorest, most isolated schools in the country.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A bookkeeping change at the Education Department will kick hundreds of rural school districts out of a federal program that for nearly two decades has funneled funding to some of the most geographically isolated and cash-strapped schools in the United States.

headline.main: Education Dept. to Cut Off Federal Funding for Some Rural Schools
headline.print_headline: Change at Education Dept. Would Cut Off Financing to Some Rural Schools

docs.abstract: The White House’s attempt to impose a more disciplined approach to communications about the virus was undermined by President Trump, who complained the news media was overstating the threat.
docs.snippet: The White House’s attempt to impose a more disciplined approach to communications about the virus was undermined by President Trump, who complained the news media was overstating the threat.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The White House moved on Thursday to tighten control of coronavirus messaging by government health officials and scientists, directing them to coordinate all statements and public appearances with the office of Vice President Mike Pence, according to several officials familiar with the new approach.

headline.main: Pence Will Control All Coronavirus Messaging From Health Officials

docs.snippet: An appeals court dismissed a lawsuit brought by the House Judiciary Committee against President Trump’s former White House counsel, Donald F. McGahn II.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A federal appeals court ruled on Friday that Congress could not sue to enforce its subpoenas of executive branch officials, handing a major victory to President Trump and dealing a severe blow to the power of Congress to conduct oversight.

docs.abstract: It is hard to discern a strategy that will accomplish the Trump administration’s objectives: renegotiating the nuclear deal with Iran or dialing back Iran’s malign behavior in the region.
docs.snippet: It is hard to discern a strategy that will accomplish the Trump administration’s objectives: renegotiating the nuclear deal with Iran or dialing back Iran’s malign behavior in the region.
docs.lead_paragraph: President Trump likes to say that Iran is “a different country” after 18 months of punishing American sanctions, and the protests sweeping Iranian cities suggest he may be right. Even his most vociferous critics acknowledge that Mr. Trump’s “maximum pressure” campaign helped fuel that unrest.

headline.main: Sanctions May Have Fueled Iran Protests, but Have Yet to Further U.S. Goals
headline.print_headline: Iran Sanctions Led to Protests, but Not U.S. Goals

docs.abstract: The investigation into President Trump and Ukraine is charging forward this week. If you tuned out over the Thanksgiving holiday, here’s what you missed.
docs.snippet: The investigation into President Trump and Ukraine is charging forward this week. If you tuned out over the Thanksgiving holiday, here’s what you missed.
docs.lead_paragraph: The inquiry will soon be transferred to the House Judiciary Committee. The core investigative work and public hearings are for now concluded, which means that the Judiciary Committee will begin considering articles of impeachment in the coming weeks. Its first public event will be Wednesday, a hearing that will feature four scholars discussing the constitutional standards for impeachment.

headline.main: Catch Up on the Impeachment Inquiry

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Attorney General William P. Barr has told Justice Department officials that he is skeptical of a conclusion by the department’s inspector general that the F.B.I. had sufficient information to open the investigation into whether any Trump associates conspired with Russia during the 2016 presidential race, according to two people familiar with the conversations.
